    "body": "@karalabe I've been fully synced many times without showing a balance.  This seems to be caused by fast mode. I was using mist wallet which comes with geth and therefore defaults to fast.  I finally tried to engineer a correct sync by uninstalling everything except backups of my keystore and starting over using a full sync, and manually added peers. This seems to be working so far.  Fast sync NEVER entered full mode even after fully synced. That is probably the core of the bug. My balance did show in light mode, but that doesn't really count since the wallet isn't synced and there are very few light peers.\r\n\r\nEither way, I'm not even sure that full mode is working because it says I have no states.\r\n```\r\n\r\n> eth.syncing\r\n{\r\n  currentBlock: 1228261,\r\n  highestBlock: 5428668,\r\n  knownStates: 0,\r\n  pulledStates: 0,\r\n  startingBlock: 0\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt does have more CPU usage than previous syncs and is reporting something other than zero for getBlock(\"latest\")",
